race.comment: MAGIC SPEED (4) opened this preparation with an easy win here and then was well supported at Hawkesbury but disappointed at the business end when placed under pressure (vet cleared). Her jockey recommended a tongue tie be applied next start, and that's eventuated. She will be fitter and back to familiar surroundings will prove a tough nut to crack. SOOO CRAZY (2) showed good early muster and fought on beaten just 1L over 1000m at Canberra. He will lead or box seat from an inside gate and can be right in the finish. VIOLET AND BLUE (1) has won her last two in the country. The latest at Orange was a big effort after missing the jump. She led the one prior, and the 3kg claim is handy. Has to be considered as well. OAKEYS CHOICE (7) was within range at Canberra and here last time. Peaks for this and will carry just 52kgs this grade with a 3kg claim atop. That brings him into it.
